<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-12580] Fix merkle tree size calculation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-12580</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5263&quot; title=&quot;Increase merkle tree depth as needed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-5263&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-5263&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; it was introduced dynamic merkle tree sizing based on estimated number of partitions as &lt;tt&gt;estimatedDepth = lg(numPartitions)&lt;/tt&gt;, but on &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-2.1/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/db/compaction/CompactionManager.java#L1052&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;CompactionManager.doValidationCompaction&lt;/a&gt; this is being calculated as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;int depth = numPartitions &amp;gt; 0 ? (int) Math.min(Math.floor(Math.log(numPartitions)), 20) : 0;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is actually calculating &lt;tt&gt;ln(numPartitions)&lt;/tt&gt; (base-e) instead of &lt;tt&gt;lg(numPartitions)&lt;/tt&gt; (base-2), which causes merkle trees to lose resolution, what may result in overstreaming.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13001754">CASSANDRA-12580</key>
            <summary>Fix merkle tree size calculation</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
